# Use nested lists to store a set of 4 (x,y) coordinates
# that, when connected, form a square. Store these coordinates
# in a variable called SquareCoordinateList. 
SquareCoordinateList =[[1,1],[1,-1],[-1,-1],[-1,1]]
# Edit the (x,y) corrdinates using mathematics to make
# the square have four times the area. Store these coordinates in 
# a variable called FourTimesSquare
for x in SquareCoordinateList:
    x[0] = x[0] * 4
    x[1] = x[1] * 4
print(SquareCoordinateList)
